HEADWORD: Compound control
<hw>Com"pound con*trol"</hw>. <fld>(A⟦eum⟧ronautics)</fld> <def>A system
of control in which a separate manipulation, as of a rudder, may be
effected by either of two movements, in different directions, of a
single lever, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

